The template was generated by running:
$ xgettext --language=Shell  --output=$PROJECT_HOME/po/raspi-config.pot $PROJECT_HOME/raspi-config

= Romanian translation =
To create an empty file for Romanian:
$ cd $PROJECT_HOME/po/; LANG=ro_RO.UTF-8 msginit
$ msginit -l ro -i $PROJECT_HOME/po/raspi-config.pot -o $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po
Then edit the translation:
$ vim $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po

== Compile, install and test the translation ==
Compile the translate file and install to the locale folder:
$ msgfmt -c -o $PROJECT_HOME/locale/ro/LC_MESSAGES/raspi-config.mo $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po
$ sudo msgfmt -c -o /usr/share/locale/ro/LC_MESSAGES/raspi-config.mo $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po
Test the translation by running raspi-config with Romanian localization:
$ sudo LANG=ro_RO.UTF-8 TEXTDOMAINDIR=$PROJECT_HOME/locale/ro $PROJECT_HOME/raspi-config # This does not work properly
$ sudo LANG=ro_RO.UTF-8 $PROJECT_HOME/raspi-config

== Updates for Romanian translation ==
Backup the old transaltion
$ mv $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro-old.po
Update the translation
$ msginit -l ro -i $PROJECT_HOME/po/raspi-config.pot -o $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po
$ msgmerge  --output-file=$PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro-old.po $PROJECT_HOME/po/raspi-config.pot
$ vim $PROJECT_HOME/po/ro.po
Compile, install and test the new translation (see above)
